{"lemma":"مُعادٍ","slug":"مُعادٍ","root":"ع.#.د","root_slug":"ع-_-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-د","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُعادٍ","root":"عود","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30953"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَادَ (ʕāda) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"with definite article (أَدَاة اَلتَّعْرِيف): the afterworld, the hereafter"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of عَادَ (ʕāda)."},"ipa":["/ma.ʕaːd/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30953","headword_ar":"مَعَادٌ","root":"Ewd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEowadN","text_ar":"مَعْوَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawodN","text_ar":"عَوْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first and third sentences. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing, returns: a place, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"result, to which a person,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing, eventually comes; a place of destination,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ultimate state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marojiEN","text_ar":"مَرْجِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSiyrN","text_ar":"مَصِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, O, K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaEaAdu","text_ar":"المَعَادُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [particularly]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ultimate state of existence, in the world to come;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA=xirapu","text_ar":"الا=خِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K, TA;) [and] so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAdu Alxaloqi","text_ar":"مَعَادُ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place to which one comes on the day of resurrection."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) the conquest of which was promised to the Prophet: (TA:) so called because the pilgrims return to it. (O.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laraAd~uka A_ilaY maEaAdK","text_ar":"لَرَادُّكَ اـِلَى مَعَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxviii. 85], is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will assuredly return thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restore thee, to Mekkeh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEAd","text_ar":"معاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"here means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Paradise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy fixed place in Paradise:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(I'Ab, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the place of thy birth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy home and town:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy usual state in which thou wast born:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thy original condition among the sons of Háshim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to most of the expositors, the words mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will assuredly raise thee from the dead."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pilgrimage."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAdN","text_ar":"مَعَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAdapN","text_ar":"مَعَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of wailing for a dead person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, A, TA:) so called because people return to it time after time: (Lth, * A:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAwidu","text_ar":"مَعَاوِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) [Hence,] one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA=li fulaAnK maEaAdapN","text_ar":"لِا=لِ فُلَانٍ مَعَادَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affliction has happened to the family of such a one, the people coming to them in the places of wailing for the dead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in other places, and the women talking of him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Fr","Th","Lth","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}